  "prompt": "What is the best Perl web app framework?",
  "response": "When considering the best Perl web application framework, several factors come into play, such as ease of use, community support, performance, and feature set. Based on these criteria, one of the most popular and widely recommended Perl web frameworks is **Mojolicious**.\n\nHere's why Mojolicious stands out:\n\n1. **Modern and Full-Featured**: Mojolicious is a modern, full-featured web framework that supports both synchronous and asynchronous programming paradigms.\n\n2. **Real-Time Web**: It has built-in support for real-time web features like WebSockets, making it suitable for developing modern web applications.\n\n3. **Easy to Learn and Use**: Mojolicious has a gentle learning curve and is easy to get started with, even for those new to Perl web development.\n\n4. **Active Community and Development**: The framework has an active community and is actively maintained, ensuring it stays up-to-date with the latest web development trends.\n\n5. **Built-in Testing**: It comes with a powerful built-in testing framework, making it easier to write and maintain tests for your web applications.\n\n6. **Flexibility**: Mojolicious is flexible enough to be used for building anything from small web applications to large-scale systems.\n\n7. **Documentation**: Excellent documentation is available, making it easier for developers to learn and use the framework effectively.\n\nHere's a simple example of a Mojolicious web application to give you a taste of how it works:\n\n```perl\nuse Mojolicious::Lite;\n\n# Route to the root URL\nget '/' => sub {\n    my $c = shift;\n    $c->render(text => 'Hello, Mojolicious!');\n};\n\n# Start the Mojolicious application\napp->start;\n```\n\nTo run this application, save it as `app.pl` and execute it with:\n\n```sh\nmorbo app.pl\n```\n\nThis will start a development server, and you can access your application at `http://localhost:3000`.\n\nWhile Mojolicious is highly recommended, it's worth noting that other frameworks like **Catalyst** and **Dancer** also have their strengths and might be more suitable depending on your specific needs and preferences. Catalyst, for instance, is known for its component-based architecture and suitability for large applications, while Dancer is praised for its simplicity and lightweight nature.\n\nIn conclusion, for most developers looking to build Perl web applications, Mojolicious offers a great balance of features, ease of use, and performance, making it an excellent choice.",
